Happy Book Birthday to THE PIG, THE ELEPHANT, AND THE WISE CRACKING BIRD by Michael Sampson and Bonnie J. Jhonson and illustrated by Joshua Sampson!!

Meet Ogden Oink, a fun-loving, adventurous, likable piglet. He dresses and speaks as humans do, and he gets into more than his share of difficulties because he interprets figurative expressions literally, and he does not understand various meanings of polysemous (i.e., multiple-meaning) words. 

This sweet and engaging book is one for the ages!!! BECOUSE WHO DOESN'T LOVE A GOOD IDIUM? This father-son duo is one that we hopefully will see more in the future!

Pick up your copy today at your favorite book retailer!

#bookbirthday #releaseday#pubday#publicationday #newbook #idium

Audiences often ask me why I write… Stephen King answers that question here through the voice of one of his characters in his new book, Holly—“Sometimes I write a line… or more than one… once in awhile a whole poem… and I think, ‘There. I got that right.’ And it satisfies. It’s like when you have an itch in the middle of your back, and you don’t think you’ll be able to reach it, but you can, just barely, and oh man, that… that sense of relief…” @brownbookskids @brownbookspublishing @michaelsampsonbooks
